# eBox Project Context

## What is eBox?

eBox is a B2B SaaS product by Open Box Group (a global real estate software consultancy). It provides structured forms (eForms) and workflows for real estate teams using MRI software, eliminating manual data entry and spreadsheet management. The second product, eConnect, handles tenant communications powered by MRI data.

## Tech Stack

- **React 19** + **TypeScript 5.8** (JSX automatic transform)
- **Vite 6** — dev server on port 3000, host 0.0.0.0
- **React Router 7** (`react-router-dom`) — URL-based routing with `<BrowserRouter>`
- **react-helmet-async** — per-page SEO metadata (`<title>`, `<meta>`, canonical URLs)
- **Tailwind CSS** — loaded via CDN in index.html (not installed as a dependency; future improvement to install properly)
- **Lucide React** — icon library
- **Puppeteer** (dev) — build-time prerendering of static HTML
- No backend — this is a static marketing site

## Hosting & Deployment

- **Hosted on Vercel** — auto-deploys from `main` branch
- **Repo**: github.com/Growth-Experts/ebox-website (private)
- **Default branch**: main
- Vercel handles SPA fallback routing automatically
- Production build includes prerendered HTML for all routes (SEO)

## Commands

- `npm run dev` — start dev server (http://localhost:3000)
- `npm run build` — production build to dist/ + prerender all routes
- `npm run build:no-prerender` — production build without prerendering (faster, for quick checks)
- `npm run preview` — preview production build
- When adding dependencies, use `--legacy-peer-deps` (react-helmet-async declares React 18 peer dep but works fine with React 19)

