## Routing & Navigation

URL-based routing via React Router in App.tsx. Routes are defined as `<Route>` elements inside a shared `<Layout>` component.

| Route       | Path         | Component        |
|-------------|-------------|------------------|
| Home        | `/`          | Home.tsx         |
| eForms      | `/eforms`    | EFormsPage.tsx   |
| eConnect    | `/econnect`  | EConnectPage.tsx |
| About Us    | `/about`     | AboutUs.tsx      |
| Contact     | `/contact`   | ContactUs.tsx    |
| Book a Demo | `/book-demo` | BookDemo.tsx     |

- `ROUTE_PATHS` in types.ts maps `PageRoute` values to URL paths
- Navigation uses `<Link to="/path">` from react-router-dom (not callbacks)
- `Button` component accepts a `to` prop — renders as `<Link>` when provided, `<button>` otherwise
- Header uses `useLocation()` for active nav state
- `ScrollToTop` component scrolls to top on route change
- Catch-all `*` route redirects to `/`

## SEO

- Each page has `<Helmet>` from react-helmet-async with unique title, meta description, and canonical URL
- Canonical URLs use `https://eboxplatform.com` as the domain
- Build step prerenders all routes to static HTML via Puppeteer (`scripts/prerender.mjs`)
- Prerendered output: `dist/[route]/index.html` for each route
- Navigation links are proper `<a>` tags (crawlable by search engines)
- Sitemap: not yet implemented (planned for future)

